<c74object name='av.pix.sort' category='' module=''>

    <digest>
        Very basic pixel sorting
    </digest>

    <description>
        A simple and basic/naive pixel sorting/smearing effect between a pixel and neighbouring pixel.  The sorting can happen based on lightness, hue (color), saturation or all three values. This object is meant to work in a feedback loop (eg. with av.pix.feedback or your own feedback effect). The sorting should happen iteratively over a feedback loop to see the pixels smear over the screen. Disabling the filter helps to make the sorting more crispy and precise. Set the sorting direction in pixels.<br/><br/>

Note: Max 9 users can have a look at jit.fx.pixelsorting and jit.fx.ge.lineinterp for similar (and more sophisticated) effects.

    </description>
    
